name: http
metaData: A composable, multi-platform, Future-based API for HTTP requests.

name: dio
metaData: A powerful HTTP networking package, supports Interceptors, Aborting and canceling a request, Custom adapters, Transformers, etc.

name: equatable
metaData: A Dart package that helps to implement value based equality without needing to explicitly override == and hashCode.

name: path
metaData: A string-based path manipulation library. All of the path operations you know and love, with solid support for Windows, POSIX (Linux and Mac OS X), and the web.

name: pdf
metaData: A pdf producer for Dart. It can create pdf files for both web or flutter.

name: enough_media
metaData: Extensible collection of media viewers for preview and interactive experiences.

name: printing
metaData: Plugin that allows Flutter apps to generate and print documents to compatible printers on Android, iOS, macOS, Windows, and Linux, as well as web print.

name: email_validator
metaData: A simple (but correct) dart class for validating email addresses

name: xml
metaData: A lightweight library for parsing, traversing, querying, transforming and building XML documents

name: petitparser
metaData: A dynamic parser framework to build efficient grammars and parsers quickly

name: pem
metaData: PEM encoding/decoding of textual keys following RFC 7468, supporting both lax/strict-mode, and certificates chains of concatenated PEM blocks.

name: freezed
metaData: Code generation for immutable classes that has a simple syntax/API without compromising on the features.

name: built_value
metaData: Value types with builders, Dart classes as enums, and serialization. This library is the runtime dependency.

name: googleapis
metaData: Auto-generated client libraries for accessing Google APIs described through the API discovery service.

name: jiffy
metaData: Jiffy is a date time dart package for parsing, manipulating, querying and formatting dates and time.

name: retry
metaData: Utility for wrapping an asynchronous function in automatic retry logic with exponential back-off, useful when making requests over network.
